HEADWORD: Argute
<hw>Ar*gute"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>argutus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>arguere</ets>. See
<er>Argue</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Sharp; shrill.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Sagacious; acute; subtle; shrewd.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The active preacher . . . the <qex>argue</qex> schoolman.</q>
<rj><qau>Milman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Argutely</ent>⟦br⟧
